      "content": "Your feelings of shame regarding how others perceive you are valid, but this circumstance does not mean you are broken or permanent; it is simply a massive, temporary setback. Many people faced significant public disappointment and were still loved deeply by their families because their identity extends far beyond their career achievements. Please consider asking for a single, low-pressure conversation where you explain the reality without expecting a resolution immediately, as this can often break the cycle of silence and isolation.",
      "source": "target",
